@Figgy

Mistakenly thinking that the Midi has its own comment section could have something to do with the sloppy placement of the button linking to Wordplay when the Games page layout was updated. (Assuming of course that might be your point of entry!) 😉

Fwiw, the placement of said button below *all three* crossword puzzles has irked me since it came out. It is a misleading user experience – which I say as a user experience designer!

@Steve L
I personally don't like the female version of gendered terms, like emerita or actress. A lot of the time they come across as condescending, as though we need to specify that the person in question is a lady because it would usually be a man. See: poetess. Like a real poet, but a girl! Imagine that!

I also have some very personal beefs with gendered languages, but that's a rant for another day.

